    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Use with reference to mostly French art of the 1960s that is realist in the sense of appropriating materials from the environment or staging actions or happenings. This movement was announced by the publication of a short manifesto in Paris, 1960; authored by Pierre Restany, and signed by the artists Arman, François Dufrêne, Raymond Hains, Yves Klein, Martial Raysse, Daniel Spoerri, Jean Tinguely and Jacques de la Villeglé.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese con referencia al arte de los años sesenta que es realista en el sentido de destinar materiales del ambiente o en organizar acciones o happenings.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gebruik met verwijzing naar de meeste Franse kunst uit de jaren zestig, die realistisch is in de zin van het toe-eigenen van materialen uit de omgeving of het uitvoeren van acties of gebeurtenissen. Deze beweging werd in 1960 aangekondigd door de publicatie van een kort manifest in Parijs, geschreven door Pierre Restany en ondertekend door de kunstenaars Arman, François Dufrêne, Raymond Hains, Yves Klein, Martial Raysse, Daniel Spoerri, Jean Tinguely en Jacques de la Villeglé.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
